Kubectl ai
Install kubectl -ai :
curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubectl-ai/main/install.sh | bash
kubectl ai --help
Enable Gemini API in Google Cloud
Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library
Change to your gmail account
Search for Generative Language API  you will see gemini api

 
Click on gemeini api  unable geminiapi
 

 

Click on create credentials
Go to credentials  on top credentials  sleect api key

Create key and copy the key: AIzaSyA0CBzcO4vvq0UJY1pwOT65S1amxX9Znww

 
Also run these commands 
(This ensures kubectl ai can talk to Gemini models.)
gcloud auth application-default login
OR
gcloud auth application-default login --no-launch-browser

gcloud auth application-default set-quota-project <PROJECT_ID>

Run the below command:
export GEMINI_API_KEY="AIzaSyA0CBzcO4vvq0UJY1pwOT65S1amxX9Znww"
kubectl-ai --llm-provider=gemini --model=gemini-2.5-flash "list all pods in namespace default"
kubectl ai "create a deployment with 3 replicas of nginx version 1.25, expose it on port 80"


 
